description.plain:
Jade Amelia Thirlwall (born December 26, 1992), also known as JADE, is a British singer, best known as a member of the successful girl group Little Mix, which she formed alongside Leigh-Anne Pinnock, Perrie Edwards, and former member Jesy Nelson during the 8th season of The X Factor UK. They were the first band to ever win the show.

With six studio albums and a greatest hits collection, Little Mix has sold over 60 million records worldwide, solidifying their status as one of the best-selling girl groups and UK acts in history. They have achieved 14 Top 10 singles, including four that reached #1 on the charts, and all of their albums have reached the Top 5 in the UK, including one #1. Little Mix also made history as the first girl group to win the British Group award at the BRIT Awards, and they have earned a total of three BRIT Awards throughout their career.

Outside of her music career, Jade is a passionate advocate for the LGBTQ+ community, citing RuPaul as her idol, and even has appeared in the television series RuPaul’s Drag Race in 2022. In 2019, she and fellow band member Leigh-Anne joined other British celebrities in climbing Mount Kilimanjaro, raising funds for Comic Relief’s Red Nose Day. That same year, Jade launched her own cocktail bar, Red Door, in her hometown of South Shields—later rebranded as Arbeia in 2020.

In December, 2021, Little Mix announced that they would be taking a break after completing their Confetti Tour, marking the end of an era but leaving the door open for future projects.

Jade’s solo career started in July 2024, with the release of her highly anticipated debut single “Angel of My Dreams”. It would go on to receive acclamation from fans and critics alike, peaking at #7 on the UK Singles Chart, marking her first solo Top 10 hit.

songs.title: Angel Of My Dreams

description.plain:
“Angel Of My Dreams” is JADE’s debut solo single. The song reflects her love-hate relationship with the music industry, drawing from her experiences since auditioning for The X Factor in 2011 and joining Little Mix, one of the most succesful girl groups in history.

On July 2, 2024, the song was officially announced along with a snippet of it. The music video was released on the same day as the track. In the music video, JADE portrays several artists who come under the wing of a music industry mogul, possibly referencing Simon Cowell, who are discarded when the mogul finds a “better” artist.

songs.full_title: IT girl by JADE
songs.title: IT girl

description.plain:
First appearing as a snippet called “IT Girl” via YouTube/AOMD on July 23rd 2024. 3 Days later she did an interview with Irish Radio station, SPIN 103.8. In the last minute of the interview they did quick fire round questions. Where Jade confirmed that the song is not called “IT Girl”. She stated “yeah, its just a lyric from the song.”

It would later be performed LIVE in New York City as ‘That’s Showbiz Baby’

The Jade room would later also leak more of the song on December 12th via Instagram.

The song was officially announced on December 15th via JADE’s Instagram as ‘IT GIRL’

On January 3th Jade announced that song in all her social media platforms and it’s out in January 10.

In a comment left on January 4th. Jade stated “the song was written on February 9th 2023”.

songs.title: FUFN (Fuck You For Now)

description.plain:
“FUFN (Fuck You For Now)” is a maximalist pop anthem that serves as JADE’s third official solo single. It follows her efforts “IT girl” and “Fantasy.”

On February 14, 2025, Fendi partnered with JADE, launching a campaign featuring the track. During the first weeks of March, JADE teased it on social media with a TMZ-inspired article and movie poster in a cinema hall. DIY Magazine applauded the song for showcasing the artist as “one of the most enticing and fresh voices in pop right now.”

songs.full_title: Fantasy by JADE
songs.title: Fantasy

description.plain:
Described by The Face as a a transcendent disco track with Donna Summer-style vocals, “Fantasy” is the second single from JADE’s solo debut album.

The single was first teased on TikTok, when the singer posted the lyrics “bring all of that freaky shit to life” when asked to give a snippet of her second single. A few weeks later, on September 26, 2024, a snippet of the recording process of the song was posted on The Jade Room’s socials, confirming it would be the follow up single. “Fantasy” was officially announced on September 30, 2024 on JADE’s social media, along with the cover art and release date reveals.

songs.full_title: Midnight Cowboy by JADE
songs.title: Midnight Cowboy

description.plain:
“Midnight Cowboy” was surprise-released as a promotional single for Jade’s upcoming debut album. In Jade’s own words, the song is “a gift from me to you until my next single drops”.

Throughout the track, Jade adopts an empowered and sensual approach, taking control over the man she’s singing about, with multiple references to the Wild West and cowboys.

Rwandan-Scottish actor Ncuti Gatwa also contributes vocals for the song.
